Learning in Health, or J Clinic.

99
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:11,080
In 1993, he shared the Nobel
Prize in physiology of medicine

100
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:13,720
for the discovery
of split genes.

101
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,850
These are genes that--

102
00:05:15,850 --> 00:05:18,790
the genes in DNA are not
one contiguous segment

103
00:05:18,790 --> 00:05:20,780
of information as
they are in bacteria.

104
00:05:20,780 --> 00:05:22,280
In fact, they are split.

105
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:25,000
And that messenger RNA
has to be processed

106
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,520
by splicing before it can be
translated into a protein.

107
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:31,390
This fundamental discovery
would alter the course

108
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:34,060
of how we understood genetic
disease and the development

109
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:35,630
of potential treatments.

110
00:05:35,630 --> 00:05:38,560
In 2004, for this
work, he was awarded

111
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:40,430
the National Medal of Science.

112
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:44,440
You'll learn more about that
discovery from Phil shortly.

113
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:48,350
